          <p class="mb-5">I sit on a man's back, choking him, and making him carry me, and yet assure myself and others that I am very sorry for him and wish to ease his lot by any means possible, except getting off his back. --  this is how a unique inbuilt and selectively ingrained amnesia in us makes us not only ignore the ugliest of the sufferings of mankind, but makes us believe that they actually do not exist.
